# React components

## Structure

- One component per file for page-level and shared components; small local helpers (`function LegCard(...)`) may live in the same file.
- Named exports for reusable components (`export function Panel(...)`). Default export only for `App.tsx`.
- Props: inline object types for simple components; extract named interfaces when reused or exported.
- Keep components under ~250 lines; extract subcomponents or hooks when they grow.

## State

- **Zustand** for cross-page client state: credentials, favourites, UI prefs, tickers.
- **TanStack Query** (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) for REST data with loading/error states.
- **Local `useState`** for form inputs and ephemeral UI (modals, tabs).
- Effects that sync with WebSocket/REST streams are intentional — do not "fix" them to satisfy react-hooks purity rules.

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes; dark theme with zinc base (`bg-zinc-900`, `text-zinc-100`, `border-zinc-800`).
- Gains: `text-emerald-400`; losses: `text-rose-400`.
- Use `clsx(...)` for conditional classes.
- Reuse `.panel` class from `src/index.css` via the `Panel` primitive.
- Tabular numbers for prices/PnL: `tabular` class.

## Patterns to follow

```tsx
// Query + loading/error
const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery({ queryKey: ['key'], queryFn: fetchFn })
if (isLoading) return <div className="text-zinc-500">Loading…</div>
if (error) return <div className="text-rose-400">{String(error)}</div>

// Panel layout
<Panel title="Title" subtitle="optional" actions={<Button>Action</Button>}>
  {children}
</Panel>
```

## Charts

- Candle/price charts: `CandlesChart` (lightweight-charts) or `SetupChart` for annotated setups.
- Histograms, heatmaps, multi-series: `EChart` wrapper with theme from `chartTheme.ts`.
- Always dispose chart instances on unmount (handled inside wrappers — extend them, don't duplicate lifecycle logic).

## Routing

- Pages: `AnalysisPage`, `StatsPage`, `SettingsPage` — add new routes in `App.tsx` inside `AppLayout`.
